{"article_id":"W8wSq8NK7Ac543h2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Current Federal Communications Commission","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"( FCC )","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"Chairman Ajit Pai memorably told","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that `` net neutrality '' rules were `` a solution","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that wo n't work","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"to a problem","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that does n't exist . ''","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Yet in 2015 ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"despite a blessed lack of throttling of specific traffic streams , blocking of websites , and other feared behavior by internet service providers","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"( ISPs )","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and mobile carriers ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"the FCC issued net neutrality rules","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that gave the federal government the right","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"to punish business practices under Title II regulations","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"designed for the old state-enabled Bell telephone monopoly .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Now that Pai ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"who became chairman earlier this year ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"has announced an FCC vote","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"to repeal the Obama-era regulations ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"he is being pilloried by progressives , liberals , Democrats , and web giants","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"ranging from Google to Netflix to Amazon to Facebook ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"often in the name","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"of protecting an `` open internet ''","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that would let little companies and startups flourish like in the good old days","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"before Google , Netflix , Amazon , and Facebook dominated everything .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Even the Electronic Frontier Foundation","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"( EFF ) ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"which back in 2009 called FCC attempts","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to claim jurisdiction over the internet a `` Trojan Horse '' for government control ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"is squarely against the repeal .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"Pai is also being targeted by net neutrality activists ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"who have posted signs","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"naming his children by his house","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"and reportedly ordered pizzas as a nuisance :","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"I have a friend","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that lives near @ AjitPaiFCC .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Net neutrality `` activists '' posted these signs ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"featuring his children 's names ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"outside his house .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Pizzas also reportedly sent to his house every half-hour last night .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"pic.twitter.com/jWI4gV6Hvc","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"- Brendan Bordelon","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"( @ BrendanBordelon )","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"November 25 , 2017","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Yet the panic over the repeal of net neutrality is misguided for any number of reasons .","depth":3},{"id":45,"text":"First and foremost , the repeal simply returns the internet back to pre-2015 rules","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"where there were absolutely no systematic issues","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"related to throttling and blocking of sites","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"( and no , ISPs were n't to blame for Netflix quality issues in 2013 ) .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"As Pai stressed in an exclusive interview with last week ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"one major impact of net neutrality regs was a historic decline in investment in internet infrastructure ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"which would ultimately make things worse for all users .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Why bother building out more capacity","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"if there 's a strong likelihood","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"that the government will effectively nationalize your pipes ?","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Despite fears , the fact is that in the run-up to government regulation , both the average speed and number of internet connections","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"( especially mobile )","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"continued to climb","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and the percentage of Americans","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"without `` advanced telecommunications capability '' dropped from 20 percent to 10 percent between 2012 and 2014 ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"according to the FCC","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"( see table 7 in full report ) .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Nobody likes paying for the internet or for cell service ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"but the fact is that services have been getting better","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"and options have been growing for most people .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Second ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"as contributor Thomas W. Hazlett , a former chief economist for the FCC , writes in The New York Daily News ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"even FCC bureaucrats do n't know what they 're talking about .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Hazlett notes","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"that in a recent debate former FCC Chairman Tom Wheeler ,","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"who implemented the 2015 net neutrality rules","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"after explicit lobbying by President Obama ,","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"the rise of AOL to dominance during the late 1990s proved the need for the sort of government regulation","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"he imposed .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"But `` AOL 's foray only became possible","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"when regulators in the 1980s peeled back 'Title II ' mandates , the very regulations","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"that Wheeler 's FCC imposed on broadband providers in 2015 , ''","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"writes Hazlett .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"`` AOL 's experiment started small","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"and grew huge ,","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"discovering progressively better ways","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"to serve consumers .","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"Wheeler 's chosen example of innovation demonstrates how dangerous it is to impose one particular platform ,","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"freezing business models in place . ''","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Deep confusion reigns on this point .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"In an explainer video","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"posted earlier this year by the Wall Street Journal ,","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"net neutrality is analogized to package delivery .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"The overnight shipper , FedEx , delivers boxes to Amazon 's customers ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"treating them all the same .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"This ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"says the video ,","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"is exactly what net neutrality rules","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"applied to ISPs","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"do .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"Wrong .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"FedEx is unregulated .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"The firm chooses to offer terms and conditions","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"that apply generically .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"Its rival , UPS , not so much :","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"`` UPS is not a common carrier , ''","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"says the company 's website ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"`` and reserves the right in its absolute discretion","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"to refuse carriage to any shipment","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"tendered to it for transportation . ''","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"The firms are free to blaze different trails ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"with markets deciding the outcome .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"And watch/read an interview with Hazlett from earlier this year","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"where he discusses his epic history of the FCC , The Political Spectrum ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"and argues","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"that deregulation gave us cable , HBO , and the iPhone .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Indeed , even more worrying than the decline in investment","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"following the implementation of net neutrality","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"is the attempt by its supporters","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"to assume","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that the current moment is how internet access will forever be delivered .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"Last year , for instance , mobile traffic surpassed fixed","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"( or desktop )","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"traffic for the first time ,","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"so the territory is changing fast .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Pai told about a variety of moves","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"that will allow for new ways","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"to deliver the internet , especially to rural areas","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"that are currently lagging behind .","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"He also noted to","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that many of the legal actions","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"lobbed at mobile carriers by net neutrality proponents","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"have been to challenge `` zero-rating '' plans","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"that allow customers to stream unlimited amounts of music , video , and other services","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"without counting against a monthly data cap .","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"Exactly how such services are bad is unclear ,","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"especially since they do n't block or throttle anything .","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"In most contexts , giving customers something extra and unlimited is usually considered a good thing .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"For Pai , repealing net neutrality is n't being done","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"to bolster the bottom line of ISPs .","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"Rather , it 's to enable the very sort of innovation and experimentation","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"that has worked so well from the early days of the commercialized internet .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"As Hazlett suggests ,","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"giving the government the ability","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"to regulate business models","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"is rarely a good idea , especially in fast-changing tech fields ;","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"there will be many competing models","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"and many will die","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"while some flourish .","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"Pai 's FCC would still insist on transparency from ISPs","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"and the Federal Trade Commission","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"( FTC )","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"would be able to investigate anti-competitive practices by ISPs","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"( Pai says","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"that the FTC is actually better suited to this sort of role than the FCC ,","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"which is open to question ) .","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"And in his interview with , Pai also laid out some benchmarks","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"by which to judge","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"whether the repeal of net neutrality is successful or not .","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"Listen below ,","depth":2},{"id":156,"text":"read a full transcript here ,","depth":3},{"id":157,"text":"or go to iTunes","depth":5},{"id":158,"text":"and subscribe to the Podcast","depth":5},{"id":159,"text":"and never miss our thrice-weekly conversations about politics , culture , and ideas from a libertarian perspective .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":319,"left":314,"right":318,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":314,"left":203,"right":313,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":174,"right":202,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"paren